🧩 Problem: Squares of a Sorted Array

Given an integer array nums sorted in non-decreasing order, return an array of the squares of each number, also sorted in non-decreasing order.

📥 Input
An integer array nums
Sorted in non-decreasing order (can include negative numbers)

📤 Output
Return a new array where:
Each element is the square of the original
The result is sorted

Example 1:
Input: nums = [-4,-1,0,3,10]
Output: [0,1,9,16,100]

Solution:
fun main() {
	val nums = intArrayOf(-4,-1,0,3,10)
    val result = IntArray(nums.size)
   	var i = 0
    var j = nums.size - 1
    var k = j
    while(i<=j){
        val left = nums[i] * nums[i]
        val right = nums[j] * nums[j]
        
        if(left > right){
            result[k] = left
            i++
        }else{
            result[k] = right
            j--
        }
        k--
    }
    print(result.toList())
   
}
